w16cs350.datatype

Class A_LatitudeLongitude

  • java.lang.Object
    • w16cs350.datatype.A_LatitudeLongitude
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<A_LatitudeLongitude>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Latitude, Longitude

    public abstract class A_LatitudeLongitude
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<A_LatitudeLongitude>
    Defines the shared elements of latitude and longitude encoded in NMEA 0183 format. The equation is NMEA = ((degrees * 100) + minutes + (seconds / 60)).

    The world is considered to be flat without distortion.
